author: Google
description:
Filmmaker Justin Hackney of Wonder Studio sits down with Dr. Arathi Sethumadhavan, Google Research Scientist, to break down the making of Lewis Capaldi’s “Something in the Heavens (Re-Imagined).” The conversation covers a lot of ground, including Justin’s take on how AI actually raises the ceiling for creativity and why he thinks filmmakers should not “throw out the rulebook” of traditional filmmaking, composition, lighting, storytelling when it comes to working with AI.

Over the coming weeks, we're sharing unique workflows and tips from more creators pushing their boundaries. Make sure to follow so you don't miss the next episode!

title: Justin Hackney on AI Filmmaking with Flow | In the Flow
